added.title: Slay Cheese
added.description: It's picture day at Acme Loo! Babs accidentally shrinks herself, Buster fails to get the perfect photo day haircut, Plucky gives lessons on being direct, and Hamton struggles to find his photo persona.

added.title: Skulls And Sillybones
added.description: Buster, Plucky, and Hamton join an exclusive secret society but soon realize that the perks promised aren't worth the sacrifices. Meanwhile, Babs and Sweetie start their own public society that becomes a big hit on campus.

added.title: Gobble Head
added.description: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

added.title: Baby Brother Blues
added.description: When Beth is told that the impending arrival of a baby brother is about to ruin her life, she runs away to find a new family.

added.title: Undercover Supervillains
added.description: The spies go undercover as supervillains, but Alex puts the mission in jeopardy when she enjoys being a baddie a little too much! Will she remember how to be good in time to save the mission?

added.title: Oversimulated Much
added.description: Clover feels that Zerlina doesn't take her seriously as a spy and is determined to prove herself at WOOHP Training Day. But when the simulations go wrong and agents blank out, the Spies realize a secret mastermind is causing the chaos.

added.title: Big Winner
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby give Muscle Man a lottery ticket for his birthday.

added.title: The Best Burger in the World
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to finish their chores before they can have burgers.

added.title: Replaced
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby find out that Benson is going to replace them and have to figure out a way to stop it.

added.title: Trash Boat
added.description: Rigby changes his name so that he can be cooler.

added.title: Fists of Justice
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to do all of Skips' duties for the day.

added.title: Yes Dude Yes
added.description: Mordecai wants to find a new girl to get over Margaret.

added.title: Busted Cart
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby bust up the cart while doing stunts and have to figure out a way to fix it.

added.title: Dead at Eight
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to babysit Death's kid.

added.title: Access Denied
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to go to Margaret's birthday party at an exclusive club.

added.title: Muscle Mentor
added.description: Rigby gets mentored by Muscle Man.

added.title: Voided
added.description: Ben goes into the Null Void to aid the Plumber's Helpers defeat D'Void.

added.title: Inside Man
added.description: Ben and company rescue Tyler, a runaway prisoner of the DNAliens while trying to stop them from completing the Jump Gate.

added.title: Birds of a Feather
added.description: Ben and company help the prince of the arachna-chimps, Simian, return to power.

added.title: Unearthed
added.description: Ben and company need to return a baby monster to its parents before the DNAliens find it.

added.title: War of the Worlds Part 1
added.description: Ben must recruit the other Plumber's kids to help stop the Highbreed invasion of Earth.

added.title: War of the Worlds Part 2
added.description: Ben and his team travel to the Highbreed home world to stop them once and for all.

added.title: Bat-Buds Forever
added.description: Bibi and Batwing must work together to get past the Legion of Zoom in order to deliver a new giant screen to Batcomputer.

added.title: MacBarm's Day Off/Playhouse Problems
added.description: It's MacBarm's day off and Zee takes over harvesting carrots with his Zee mobile, but when it breaks, the work still needs to be done./Ranger Nat is bringing a playhouse on the train for Timmy and Izzy, but it won't fit through the tunnel!

added.title: Mixed Signals
added.description: The team receives a video message from Tenderheart that their mission has successfully ended and they can return home. Cheer suspects something about the message is wrong, but other members of the team don't agree. Cheer courageously stands her ground and keeps the team together while she solves the mystery, and reveals the message was faked by Bluster.

added.title: Lights Out
added.description: When a blackout upends Vivie's evening plans, Barney helps the kids pivot to night games and a campout. The night is made even more special by friends in the community, who come together and make the best out of the unexpected event.

added.title: Bat-Blast-Off!
added.description: When King Tut steals an ancient artifact that makes his Carcophagus magically fast, MOE equips Bam with rocket boosters to catch the villain and Bam must learn how to control all that speed.

added.title: Nobody's Perfect
added.description: When Cheer makes some simple mistakes, she begins to lose confidence in her piloting skills and herself. The self-doubt becomes so severe, she decides to step away from her role as pilot of the Cloudseeker. But the Team needs her, the Whiffles need her, and she must regain her self-confidence so they can stop Bluster's latest nefarious scheme.
